text: Selina-Maria Edbauer (born 11 March 1998), known professionally as Salena, is an Austrian singer and songwriter. In 2017, Salena participated in the TV show The Voice of Germany. In 2021, she competed in the Austrian talent show Starmania, where she met Austrian singer Teya. In 2023, it was announced that she would represent Austria in Eurovision 2023, alongside Teya, with the song "Who the Hell is Edgar?". They were runners-up in the second semi-final and finished in 15th place in the Grand Final. She released two more songs with Teya ("Bye Bye Bye" and "Ho Ho Ho") before they began solo careers. == References == Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:Austrian singers Category:Eurovision Song Contest entrants
